According to the screenshot provided, the browser we need to double-click to open is the Firefox Web Browser. On the screen, the Firefox icon is located in the upper left corner. To do this, we need to move the mouse to the location of the Firefox icon and double-click. The following JSON format instructions are used to perform this operation:```json
[
    {"action_type": "MouseAction", "mouse_action_type": "double_click", "mouse_button": "left", "mouse_position": {"width": 63, "height": 42}}
]
```This operation assumes that the icon is roughly at the '(63,42)' position of the screen coordinate.
